captions.text:
- Right now I'm going
to bring out two people
who always make me so happy.

Here to dance for you are
4-year-old Heaven
and her mom Tianne.
[cheers and applause]
[Beyonce's "7/11" starts]

[Beyonce singing on recording]
Shoulders sideways,
Smack it, smack it in the air

Legs moving side to side,
Smack it in the air

Legs moving side to side,
Smack you in the air

Shoulders sideways,
Smack it, smack it in the air
Smack it, smack it in the air

Legs moving side to side,
Smack it, smack it in the air
Smack it, smack it in the air

Wave your hands side to side,
Put it in the air

Wave your hands
Side to side, put it in the air

Clap, clap, clap
Like you don't care

Smack that, clap, clap, clap
Like you don't care
I know you care
Clap, clap, clap, clap, clap it

Foot up
My foot up

Hold up now
My foot up

I'm spinning
My foot up

Foot up yeah
My foot up

I'm spinning
My foot up

Put my foot down yeah
My hands up

My hands up
My hands up

Flexing
Flexing while my hands up

My hands up
My hands up
I stand up with my hands up

Then I put up
My hands up

I put up
My hands up

Shoulders sideways,
Smack it, smack it in the air

Legs moving side to side,
Smack it in the air
[music continues]

[lip synchs]
Sweating out my blow out
Sweating out my press

This trick about to go off
Mad cause I'm so fresh
Fresher than you
I'm fresher than you
Fresher than you, ho
[cheers and applause]
- Oh!
Oh, my God!
- Hi.
- Well, I mean--

I cannot believe you're--
here, turn around,

let everybody see how pretty
you are.

Four years old!
- [giggles]

- How do you remember all
those things?

- Um, I was teaching class,
and my mom taught it to me.

- Oh, right.
You were teaching class?

She's teaching class now.
Wow, that's amazing.

What's new in your life?
What's going on?

- Um, I have a brother,
and my family.

- Uh huh.
- And I miss him out here today.

- Okay.
(audience) Aw!

- And he's not a human,
he's a puppy.
[laughter and applause]

- And you call him your brother?
- Yes.

- Well, they're like family
members, aren't they?

- Yes.
- They're just so sweet.
And what's your doggie's name?

- Cody.
- Cody?
That's great, did you name Cody?

- Yes.
My mom named him, too.

- You named him by--
his last name.
What's his last name?
- Cody Posay.

- Cody Posay,
he has a last name.

Well, if he gets mail,
that's important, I guess.
[laughter]

So do you think you're going to
be a dancer when you grow up?

- I am a dancer!
- Ah, I'm sorry.
[applause]

What else do you want to do
when you grow up?

- I want to be a star,
and a driver.

[laughter]
- A star and a driver?

Wow.
Why do you want to be a driver?

- Because every time when my mom
drives in a car,

I pretend when I'm--
I'm driving with her, too.
- Oh, okay.

So you want to be
a professional driver?

- Yes.
- Okay, well, I got you a gift,
so you can practice, okay?

- Okay.
- And your colors,
your favorite colors are what?

- Pink and purple.
- Well, look at this!
[cheers and applause]

- All right.
- Nice.

- Thanks for being here.
Come back and see us any time.
We'll be right back after this.
